=\"Autoblog\" data-title=\"Rivian R1T\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1334\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjA5MTIyNzIxMzQxMzE5MDEy/rivian-r1t-reveal.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02e6f40220082764\" data-image-slug=\"Rivian R1T reveal\" data-public-id=\"MjA5MTIyNzIxMzQxMzE5MDEy\" data-source-name=\"Autoblog\" data-title=\"Rivian R1T Interior\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1125\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NjUzMDI4/rivian-r1t-reveal.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02e6f40210082764\" data-image-slug=\"Rivian R1T reveal\" data-public-id=\"MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NjUzMDI4\" data-source-name=\"Autoblog\" data-title=\"R1T Frunk\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"photos-rivian-r1s-and-rivian-r1t\"\u003ePhotos: Rivian R1S and Rivian R1T\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/ar_16:9%2Cc_fill%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_406%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMTY4NjE4NjIzNzA2MTQz/rivian-r1s.jpg\" alt=\"Rivian R1S\" itemprop=\"image\" loading=\"lazy\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Scout trucks are both longer than their Rivian counterparts – the Traveler is around 7 inches longer than the R1S, and the Terra is over 12 inches longer than the R1T. In fact, the new Scout trucks are…well, \u003cem\u003ehuge\u003c/em\u003e. They’re also wider than the Rivian trucks. The Traveler measures 91.6 inches wide compared to the \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/reviews/2025-rivian-r1s-ev-suv-pros-and-cons\"\u003eRivian R1S\u003c/a\u003e at 81.8. The R1T measures 79 inches across, compared to the Terra which measures the same 91.6 inches. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eFor context, a \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/ford/\"\u003eFord\u003c/a\u003e Raptor’s width \u003cem\u003eincluding the mirrors \u003c/em\u003eis 96 inches even. We have to assume these measurements include mirrors, but either way, the Terra and Traveler will be easy to tell apart from the Rivian duo.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"scout-interior-layout-takes-a-similar-minimalist-approach\"\u003eScout interior layout takes a similar minimalist approach\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Scout trucks and Rivian trucks are very similar once you’re behind the wheel. Dual screens dominate the cabin, and it looks like materials in the Scout Terra and Scout Traveler will be about on par with what we already get in the R1S and R1T. Without hard measurements we can’t say for sure, but the Scout truck’s larger dimensions might pay dividends in passenger comfort and interior cargo space. Terra and Traveler get some cool switch hardware that’s absent from the button-less Rivian trucks. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Rivian interiors are cool, but the switches inside the Scout cabins look might satisfying. \" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.jpg\" height=\"4082\" width=\"6123\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003eRivian interiors are cool, but the switches inside the Scout cabins look might satisfying. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eScout Motors\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"performance-and-range-comparisons-are-preliminary-but-rivian-has-an-edge\"\u003ePerformance and range comparisons are preliminary, but Rivian has an edge\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThings start getting further apart when you look at performance figures. We only have the basics when it comes to the Scout models: zero to 60 mph in 3.5 seconds and up to 1,000 pound-feet of torque. If we’re comparing top trims, the R1T and R1S trucks sprint from zero to 60 mph in 2.5 seconds thanks to an available 1,125 pound-feet of torque.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv phx-gallery=\"\"\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1333\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzQ0MzQ0MDMyNDYw/scout-terra.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef35e000264e\" data-image-slug=\"Scout Terra\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzQ0MzQ0MDMyNDYw\" data-title=\"Scout Terra\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1333\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzQ0MzQzNzcwNzAy/scout-terra-2-exterior.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef35a00024cc\" data-image-slug=\"scout terra 2 exterior\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzQ0MzQzNzcwNzAy\" data-title=\"Scout Terra\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1333\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzQ0MzQzODM2MjM4/scout-terra-bed.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef35900124cc\" data-image-slug=\"Scout Terra Bed\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzQ0MzQzODM2MjM4\" data-title=\"Scout Terra\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1501\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzg5NDQwOTkyODQ2/scout-traveler-int-1.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef40100024cc\" data-image-slug=\"Scout Traveler int 1\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzg5NDQwOTkyODQ2\" data-title=\"Scout Terra/Traveler Interior\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1333\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NTU5Mzc0/scout-traveler-int-5.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef40a000264e\" data-image-slug=\"Scout Traveler int 5\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NTU5Mzc0\" data-title=\"Scout Terra/Traveler Interior\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1333\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzg5NDQwOTI3MzEw/scout-traveler-1.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef400000264e\" data-image-slug=\"Scout Traveler 1\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzg5NDQwOTI3MzEw\" data-title=\"Scout Traveler\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1333\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzg5NDQwOTI2OTI0/scout-traveler-2.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef3ff00024cc\" data-image-slug=\"Scout Traveler 2\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzg5NDQwOTI2OTI0\" data-title=\"Scout Traveler\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1125\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef613000264e\" data-image-slug=\"Scout-EV_Group_0748 FINAL 2\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy\" data-source-name=\"Scout Motors\" data-title=\"Scout Traveler/Terra\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-caption-html=\"\" data-full-height=\"1333\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy/scout-traveler-int-3.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02eaef407000264e\" data-image-slug=\"Scout Traveler int 3\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjQzMzg5NzA5NDI4MzAy\" data-source-name=\"Scout Motors\" data-title=\"Cool switches inside the Scouts.\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"photos-scout-terra-and-scout-traveler\"\u003ePhotos: Scout Terra and Scout Traveler\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/ar_16:9%2Cc_fill%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_406%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjQzMzQ0MzQ0MDMyNDYw/scout-terra.jpg\" alt=\"Scout Terra\" itemprop=\"image\" loading=\"lazy\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe story remains the same with range, too. Though Scout Motors says a hybrid version of the truck will be able to roam 500 miles between fill-ups and charges, all-electric range hovers around 350 miles. That isn’t bad until you look at the max range on Rivian trucks, which is upwards of 400 miles. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2025 Rivian R1S\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjA5MzAxMzEzMzI5MTEyMjcw/2025-rivian-r1s.jpg\" height=\"2795\" width=\"4192\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003e2025 Rivian R1S interior\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eKyle Edward\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"screens-and-software-are-similar-but-not-identical\"\u003eScreens and software are similar, but not identical\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eScout says the Terra and Traveler will receive their own interface – Scout Community UX. We don’t know anything more about it, and we don’t have any idea what kind of driver aids might come packaged with the two trucks. Sources are indicating that the Scout trucks might have bigger screens, but we don’t have confirmation of that. All of the trucks get a 12.3-inch digital gauge cluster behind the wheel. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cphoenix-super-link href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/reviews/2025-rivian-r1s-ev-suv-pros-and-cons\" onclick=\"return window.phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" phx-track-id=\"Embed Card Click\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-super-link\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"pricing-needs-to-hold-steady-at-60-000-for-the-traveler-and-terra-to-remain-dominant\"\u003ePricing needs to hold steady at $60,000 for the Traveler and Terra to remain dominant\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eOne place the Scout Terra and Scout Traveler seem to surely outpace Rivian is pricing. Both are said to start under $60,000, making them significantly less expensive than the R1S or R1T. Those trucks start at $75,900 and $69,900, respectively. That said, the pair of Scouts are still three years out from scheduled start of production. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"The Terra (background) and Traveler (foreground). \" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjQzNTMyMjQ4NTg5OTAy/scout-ev_group_0748-final-2.jpg\" height=\"4349\" width=\"7731\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003eThe Terra (background) and Traveler (foreground). \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eScout Motors\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThere’s room in the market for all four of these electrified \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/features/toyota-land-cruiser-vs-toyota-4runner\"\u003eoff-roaders\u003c/a\u003e. Despite some similarities, the pricing and performance capabilities alone set each truck apart from the next. How much market share Scout steals from Rivian will be very dependent on market conditions and final pricing. After all, a lot can happen in three years. Especially when you consider Scout’s parent company, Volkswagen, has seen better days. We look forward to getting hands-on time with the new Scout SUV and truck.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cphoenix-super-link href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/features/scout-motors-breaks-ground-on-new-2-billion-plant-in-south-carolina\" onclick=\"return window.phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" phx-track-id=\"Embed Card Click\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-super-link\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003csection id=\"phximagetilehub-3\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-hub data-group-size=\"9\" data-first-group-size=\"9\"\u003e\u003csection\u003e\u003cphoenix-non-personalized-recommendations-no-tracking config=\"{\u0026#34;siteBasePath\u0026#34;:null,\u0026#34;size\u0026#34;:3,\u0026#34;widgetName\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;tempestn_tile-hub_autoblog_article-page_title-not-found-1-1\u0026#34;}\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-non-personalized-recommendations-no-tracking\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003c/phoenix-hub\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
